  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/4531",
  "title": "InfiniteHits cache cannot get invalidated",
  "body": "## 🐛 Bug description\r\n\r\nWe have `cache` object passed to InfiniteHits, but we store the hits in `cachedHits`. So `cachedHits` becomes the second layer of cache, which cannot be invalidated. InfiniteHits always should reflect the status of `cache`.\r\n\r\n## 🔍 Bug reproduction\r\n\r\n**Steps to reproduce the behavior:**\r\n\r\n1. Go to https://codesandbox.io/s/compassionate-goldberg-bmltl?file=/src/app.js\r\n2. Click on \"Clear Cache\" button\r\n3. The hits are not refreshed.\r\n\r\n## 💭 Expected behavior\r\n\r\nWe should either get rid of `cachedHits` or make it up-to-date with `cache`.\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n- OS: macOS 10.15.7\r\n- Browser: FireFox\r\n- Version: 81.0.1 (64-bit)",
